sols_latex:
Differentiating both sides implicitly with respect to x,

\begin{align*}
\frac{d}{dx}(x^3+xy) &= \frac{d}{dx}(5x-y^3)
\\ \frac{d}{dx}(x^3)+ {\color{OliveGreen} \frac{d}{dx}(xy)} &= \frac{d}{dx}(5x)- {\color{OliveGreen} \frac{d}{dx}(y^3)}\\ 3x^2 + {\color{OliveGreen} 1 \cdot y + x \cdot \frac{d}{dx}(y)} &= 5 - {\color{OliveGreen} 3y^2 \cdot \frac{d}{dx}(y)}
\\ 3x^2 + {\color{OliveGreen} y + x \cdot\frac{dy}{dx}} &= 5 - {\color{OliveGreen} 3y^2 \cdot\frac{dy}{dx}}
\end{align*}

Solving for $\frac{dy}{dx}$ we find

\begin{align*}
x \cdot\frac{dy}{dx} + 3y^2 \cdot\frac{dy}{dx} &= 5 - 3x^2 - y
\\ \frac{dy}{dx}\cdot(x+3y^2) &= 5 - 3x^2 - y
\\ \frac{dy}{dx} &= {\color{blue} \frac{5-3x^2-y}{x+3y^2}}
\end{align*}

